race.comment: REMEMBER TOMMY (2) is a well performed dog who recorded his 11th career win last time out at Hobart (19.95). Form here at the trip sound including six wins. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. MISS CHIRPY (7) stuck on well last time to finish half a length back in second (16.22) at this track in a Grade 5 over 278m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from six starts. Can feature again. CHANGING LANES (1) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when seventh at this track over 278m behind Good Luck Babe (16.66) in a Grade 4. Better than last start and can bounce back. HIGHGATE SNIPER (3) is in the mix despite missing out at this track last time.
